9 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to ivermectin; defining term;
allowing ivermectin to be sold or purchased without
11 prescription; providing for immunity; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
12
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 355.5 of Title 59, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. As used in this section, "over-the-counter medication" means
20 medication that may be legally sold and purchased without
21 prescription.
22 B. Notwithstanding any law to the contrary, Food and Drug
23 Administration (FDA) approved ivermectin suitable for human use may
24 be sold or purchased as an over-the-counter medication in this state
HB4124 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 with out a prescription or consultation with a health care
2 professional.
3 C. Notwithstanding any other law, a pharmacy is not criminally
4 or civilly liable for supplying ivermectin in accordance with this
5 section.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
7
8 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
OVERSIGHT, dated 03/05/2026 - DO PASS, As Amended and Coauthored.
